Welcome to your November newsletter in which we share our exciting news, and invite you to help us raise the profile and impact of veganism in one simple step. Did we mention weâ€™re excited?!

Whether it was the support of stars like Sharon Osbourne, Emma Thompson, and Olivia Colman, or whether it was Generation Vegan turning up to Earthshotâ€™s New York Summit wearing Prince William masks, we donâ€™t know. What we do know is that Earthshot heard our plea that they nurture a plant-based food system to heal our planet, and they got in touch with an offerâ€¦

Earthshot has invited GenV to put forward two experts to join the judging panel for the Protect and Restore Nature category, the winner of which will receive Â£1 million. Now, there are many extraordinarily knowledgeable and talented people who could fit the bill, and we are delighted that two exceptional candidates have accepted this role: Joseph Poore from Oxford University and Dr. Hannah Ritchie from Our World in Data. Weâ€™ll be introducing you to them both soon.

GenV has also been invited to become an official nominator to the Protect and Restore Nature category. We are the first - and only - vegan group to be invited to this role, and we intend to make the most of it. Our job is to seek out the best vegan groups, initiatives, and companies from around the world and nominate them for the 2024 award. Like Santa Claus, we have already started making a list, and we will be checking it twice, but we know there are many more fantastic projects out there that we haven't yet heard of. This is where you come in.
We are inviting YOU to put forward your own favorite plant-based groups, companies, and campaigns for consideration.
If you know the perfect group and are ready to nominate, you can do that here.
If you would like to know more about GenVâ€™s Earthshot campaign, the process of nominating, or what happens next, check outour latest blog.

Thank you to everyone who has supported this campaign. Conversations with Earthshot are ongoing and we still hope to bring you news of a whole new Earthshot category dedicated to advancing a plant-based food system. But for now, we are delighted with this important progress.

On January 1st,we challenged the UK Prime Ministerto go vegan for one month in exchange for a £1 million charity donation. A plant-based agricultural system is good for our planet, its peoples, the government’s climate commitments, and animals, and £1M is a huge donation for any charity. But, in a letter from the PM’s representative - who is a sheep, beef, and egg farmer - all our concerns were sidestepped.

While the Prime Minister did not accept our challenge, our powerful message reached millions of other people through the 5,000+ ads across London, the powerful and positive media coverage in 14 countries, and social media. Thank you to everyone who shared our message, and encouraged others to move towards a vegan lifestyle.

The £1 million is safe; we will retain it for a future campaign. In the meantime, we are making sizable donations to two UK farmed animal sanctuaries to support their amazing work. Read more about the amazing work and fundraising efforts ofAmberwood AnimalsandThe Farm Animal Sanctuary.

...que trata sobre amor, compasión y espiritualidad. Conoceremos a algunos increíbles animales rescatados, compartiremos nuestras recetas favoritas para el Día de San Valentín y, como siempre, concluiremos con algunas noticias emocionantes para alegrar sus corazones

Activistas de todo Brasil se unieron para rescatar a 1,000 búfalas después de que un granjero lechero las abandonara para dejarlas morir. El caso fue complejo y requirió múltiples comparecencias ante el tribunal, mientras que las personas trabajaron incansablemente para salvar a tantos animales como fuera posible de la inanición, deshidratación, lesiones y enfermedades. Después de meses de incertidumbre, nos llenamos de alegría y nos emocionamos al ver a las búfalas liberadas en su nuevo hogar.
El 14 de febrero, que es tanto el Día de San Valentín como el inicio de la Cuaresma, lanzamos oficialmente un nuevo desafío vegano de 7 días, ¡y hoy te ofrecemos acceso anticipado!

En lugar de considerar el veganismo desde la perspectiva de los derechos de los animales, el medio ambiente, la salud o la humanidad, este desafío único lo aborda desde la perspectiva de verdades universales: amor, compasión, altruismo, asombro, sabiduría, verdad y perdón.

Por cada persona que se inscriba para participar en cualquiera de nuestros desafíos de 7 días en el próximo mes, GenV donará $1 USD para apoyar el cuidado de las búfalas en Brasil, ¡hasta $10,000 USD! ¡Son dos grandes incentivos para participar!

Since Covid-19 emerged, we have been channeling our time and our funds into providingvegan food reliefto those in need all around the world, including toMaasai communitiesin southwestern Kenya.

Today we are asking you to support us as we challenge former President Barack Obama, actress Lupita Nyong‚Äôo and musician Tom Morello - all people with Kenyan heritage - to donate $10,000 towards this relief program.

In normal times, the Maasai make and sell craft goods and trinkets to tourists but the sudden loss of visitors due to the pandemic is having a devastating impact. Maasai community leader Jack Lekishon told us‚ÄúI fear that hunger and starvation will even kill people more than the Covid-19 pandemic! Some going for weeks without food at all.‚Äù

We acted immediately, andpledged 50,000 meals(along with water, hygiene products and masks), and began working with Jack and his team of volunteersto get food to those most in need. This will provide the Maasai with short-term relief but it is not sufficient to sustain them for very long.
Now, one of our donors has said he will fund another 50,000 meals, at a cost of $10,000, if former President Barack Obama, Lupita Nyong‚Äôo or Tom Morello also agree to donate $10,000.
That means we have an amazing chance to triple our impact! But first we need to make sure our message is heard. Will you help us?

where we celebrate the heroes that run sanctuaries, take a moment to honor some recent victories for animals and our planet, and ask for your help to protect animals in need.
Can you make a small donation? We have never asked you for funds to support our own work, but today we are asking if you can spare a little for two critical rescue missions.

Colombia is facing unprecedented drought due to climate breakdown and the effect of El Niño. This has meant that one animal sanctuary must urgently relocate to provide pasture and water for their rescued cows and other animals. Read more and please donate if you can.

Stockfree Farmers does an incredible job working with farmers to transition away from animal farming and into sustainable plant farming. This often means there are animals who can be saved. Today, there are 33 sheeps who have a sanctuary space offered to them, but the sanctuary needs funds. Can you help?

Jayaseelan TD started the Ahimsa Farm Animal Sanctuary in Kerala, India, when he realized there was nowhere else he could send the animals he wanted to rescue from slaughter. There he cares for 250 animals, including bulls, buffaloes, cows, hens, turkeys, ducks, and geese.

Após meses de incerteza, ficamos muito felizes ao ver as búfalas chegando em seu novo lar.

...where we link arms with activists in the UK, unveil the campaign that threatens to sue vegans, and share some fantastic news from around the world. What are we waiting for?

The world’s oldest animal charity, the RSPCA, is defending its role in endorsing intensive farming and slaughter after an in-depth investigation by Animal Rising. The charity’s RSPCA Assured logo is stamped onto meat, milk, and eggs to reassure consumers that the animals were raised in high-welfare farms. But the reality is, of course, very different, and suffering is endemic in RSPCA Assured farms as it is on all intensive farms.
Watch our interview with journalist George Monbiot

A brand-new parody campaign is inviting meat eaters to sue vegans for any distress or harm they may have been caused. Via the fictitious law firm of Seymour Loudermilk, haters can bring legal action against preachy vegans if they have been upset by the facts of animal farming. The campaign is running in Los Angeles, and its creators hope it will “drive in-depth discussion about the real reasons vegans care so much and what we can all do, right now in our lives, to change the world.” VisitHateVegans.comand let us know what you think of it!

Between 17th and 19th September, the Green REV Institute will bring together passionate advocates, forward-thinking leaders, and innovative minds from all corners of the globe to focus on creating a plant-based future. This year, the event will focus on plant-based food and the development of the plant-based sector.

There are a lot of exciting new projects and developments in the GenV pipeline, including the release of our first ever animation narrated by a much-loved celebrity, as well as the release of a powerful new Indian documentary that we are supporting. Plus, we are launching a fun new podcast on vegan parenting! All this plus there is likely to be some exciting Earthshot-related news coming soon. We wish we could tell all but for now we’ve been sworn to secrecy.

Last year, The Earthshot Prize — Prince William’s environmental initiative — invited us to nominate two experts to their voting panel. One of the people we were delighted to put forward is Dr. Hannah Ritchie fromOur World in Data. Watch as she tells us about her vision for the future.

We hear it A LOT. “I can’t go vegan because my genetics say I should eat meat.” In this blog, we examine how diet and genetics interact, and discover what the leading twin study researcher recommends we eat.

...which is all about love, compassion, and spirituality. We’ll meet some incredible rescued animals, share our favorite Valentine’s Day recipes, and finish up, as always, with some great news to get your hearts singing.

Activists from across Brazil united to rescue 1,000 buffaloes after they were abandoned to die by a dairy farmer in Brazil. The case was complex, and required multiple court appearances, while people on the ground worked tirelessly to save as many animals as possible from starvation, dehydration, injury, and sickness. After months of uncertainty, we were jubilant—and very emotional—when we saw the buffaloes released into their new home.
On February 14th—which is both Valentine’s Day and the start of Lent—we are officially launching a brand new 7-day vegan course, but today we are offering you early access!

Instead of considering veganism from the perspective of animal rights, the environment, health, or humanity, this unique course considers it from the perspective of universal truths: love, compassion, altruism, awe, wisdom, truth, and forgiveness.

For every person who signs up to take part in any of our 7-day courses in the next month, GenV will donate $1US to support the care of the buffaloes in Brazil, up to $10,000. That’s two great incentives to take part!

And while we are thinking about Valentine’s Day, we pulled together some of our favorite recipes that are bound to impress vegans and non-vegans alike. So, whether you are spending the day with a date, a partner, a friend, your family, or alone, you can express your love with some of these beautiful meals.
We love this film made by Menkay, a former dairy owner, now vegan activist. If you do too, give him a follow at Menkay.ig and receive more thought-provoking content.
We are often asked about the connection between our food choices and reproductive justice, and so we brought together some thoughts on this issue in one easy-to-read blog. Take a look!
en el que les presentamos a Eddie, un precioso cordero rescatado del matadero, y celebramos todas las ventajas que tiene una dieta vegetal para los animales, las personas y el planeta.

En todo el mundo se sacrifican millones de corderos para la Pascua, la fiesta cristiana de la resurrección, la esperanza y la vida. Para denunciar este espantoso comercio,nuestra valiente Gerenta de Campañas en Italia fue a un mataderoy pudo rescatar a un dulce bebé, Eddie.

GenV apoyó una acción internacional contra una piscifactoría de pulpos en Las Palmas de Gran Canaria el 23 de abril. Los pulpos son seres muy sensibles y solitarios. No podemos ni debemos permitir que sufran de esta manera. Puedesvisitar la web de PACMA,firmar la peticióny usar el hashtag#StopOctopusFarmpara mostrar tu apoyo.

¿Estás al tanto de las relaciones entre la explotación a los animales y la falta de respeto por otros cuerpos? En este video, Franco Xahir Arjona Alvarado nos cuenta por qué el especismo y la transfobia están tan cerca.

En México se está llevando a cabo un conflicto muy importante. La comunidad de Sitilpech, en Mérida, está resistiendo el emplazamiento de una mega granja porcina, que albergará y asesinará a 49 mil cerdos. Entérate de todas las novedades en nuestro blog:

Nuestro trabajo de solidaridad alimentaria continúa y este mes, con el apoyo del activista local Justin Lumoo Paluku, hemos distribuido 400 comidas nutritivas a base de plantas a las personas que han sido desplazadas por la rebelión en curso M23 (conflicto armado) en Karisimbi, en la República Democrática del Congo. También hemos proporcionado comidas diarias a tres escuelas veganas en Maasai Mara (Kenia), con el apoyo del líder maasai Jack Lekishon. Descubrepor qué nos importala solidaridad alimentaria.
Esperamos que tu mes de abril también esté lleno de buenas noticias que tengan impacto en tu salud, la de los animales y la del planeta. ¡Gracias por acompañarnos hasta aquí!

Heute startet unsere neueste Kampagne! Wir werden eine Million Dollar an eine US-Veteranen-Wohltätigkeitsorganisation spenden, wenn Präsident Trump im Januar vegan wird. Unter dem Motto „Make America Healthy Again“ setzen wir uns für pflanzliche Ernährung ein – zum Wohle unserer Gesundheit, der Umwelt, der Wirtschaft und natürlich der Tiere.
Wir sind überall da, wo Präsident Trump ist!

Wir haben einen ganzseitigen offenen Brief in derNew York Timesveröffentlicht, Fernsehwerbung in Washington, D.C., New York und West Palm Beach geschaltet, sowie Plakatwände um Mar-a-Lago und dem Weißen Haus herum positioniert. Wir sorgen dafür, dass unsere Botschaft den Präsidenten erreicht!

Wir haben die Unterstützung vieler führender amerikanischer Ärzte, darunter Dean Ornish, Caldwell Esselstyn, Michael Greger, Joel Kahn, Neal Barnard sowie dem Biochemiker T. Colin Campbell. Ihre ergreifenden Plädoyers finden Sie auf unsererWebseite.

Wir haben zudem Dutzende inspirierender Filme von Menschen, deren Leben sich durch vegane Ernährung veränderte – oder gerettet wurde. Dazu gehören ehemalige US-Marines, ein Kampfpilot, ein ehemaliger Fallschirmjäger, Olympiasieger und frühere Jäger.Erfahren Sie ihre Geschichtenund lassen Sie sich inspirieren!
Unterstützt von den Animal Hero Kids

Kinder führen weltweit Kampagnen zum Schutz ihrer Zukunft an – allen voran die globalen Klimastreiks von Greta Thunberg. Wir freuen uns, mit den Animal Hero Kids eine Partnerschaft eingegangen zu sein, um jungen Menschen eine Stimme bei diesem wichtigen Thema zu geben.
Veganismus ist für jeden, nicht nur den Präsidenten

Wir hoffen sehr, dass Donald Trump im Januar vegan wird. Immerhin liebt er nichts so sehr wie einen großartigen Deal! Doch egal, ob er zusagt oder nicht, wir fordern alle Menschen auf, in den USA und darüber hinaus, im Januar vegan zu probieren. Sie können sichanmelden, um täglich einen Newsletter, Rezepte, unseren Ernährungsratgeber und das Vegane Starterkit zu erhalten. Die Teilnahme istvöllig kostenlos. Wir hoffen, eine Gesundheitsrevolution in Gang zu setzen. Kennen Sie jemanden, der daran interessiert ist, vegan zu werden? Leiten Sie diese E-Mail weiter!
Finden Sie uns auf Social Media

Folgen Sie uns, schauen Sie sich unsere bewegenden Filme an, lassen Sie sich inspirieren, teilen Sie unsere Botschaft und helfen Sie uns, Veganismus als eine wahrhaft gesunde Ernährungsweise zu präsentieren – für uns, unsere Erde und die Tiere. Unser Aufruf: #MakeAmericaHealthyAgain

en el que compartimos nuestro video, blog y cita favoritos del mes, así como algunas de las noticias más emocionantes de GenV y de todo el mundo.Estamos viviendo nuestra misión de unión, disrupción y transformación.
El más elegido por el público fue sobre feminismo y veganismo.

Este mes estamos trabajando en videos sobre veganismo y discapacidad, la comida y el colonialismo en la India, la masculinidad y el veganismo, y algunos fantásticos vídeos de recetas. Pronto los veremos todos.

Para las personas que prefieren o necesitan recetas más accesibles, hemos elaborado un libro electrónico que contiene recetas súper sabrosas sin cocción, sin picar, sólo con batidora y sólo con microondas.Puedes descargar el tuyo gratis aquí.

Nuestro trabajo de solidaridad alimentaria continúa, ya que compartimos alimentos con tres escuelas veganas en Kenia, coordinadas por nuestro director nacional local, Jack Lekishon. La sequía en Kenia está teniendo un impacto devastador y estamos recaudando fondos para ayudar a Jack a apoyar a su comunidad con alimentos basados en plantas. Si quieres, puedesdonar aquí.

Nos estamos preparando para la Cumbre de AVA en Washington DC este mes, donde, en nombre de GenV, nuestra CEO, Naomi Hallum, dictará un taller sobre “El poder de la narración audiovisual”. Para más información, hazclick aquí.También tendremos un stand de GenV y repartiremos algunos productos, así que puedes pasar a saludarnos.

Los sondeos de opinión muestran sistemáticamente que la gente no aprueba la cría industrial de animales para el sacrificio en condiciones terribles, estresantes y de hacinamiento. Esto se debe a que la mayoría de la gente se preocupa por los animales, y se describiría como amante de los animales. Sin embargo, la mayor parte de la población sigue comiendo carne, y la mayoría de la carne procede de animales criados en granjas industriales. Así que, ¿cómo podemos navegar por este enigma? ¿Qué es lo que ocurre?

En una victoria histórica para el movimiento por los derechos de los animales, dos activistas de Direct Action Everywhere (DxE) han sido absueltos esta semana de los cargos de robo y hurto que se les imputaban tras rescatar a unos cerdos enfermos de una granja de Smithfield en Utah en 2017.

El veredicto es la culminación de una persecución de cinco años por parte del FBI que comenzó después de que los activistas de DxE publicaran imágenes de vídeo que revelaban condiciones espantosas y cerdos enfermos y sufrientes dentro de la granja. Marca un punto de inflexión para nuestro movimiento al abrir la puerta a un "derecho de rescate" legal de cualquier animal que esté sufriendo.
El veredicto no sólo es muy bueno para los animales de granja, sino también para Lily y Lizzie, los dos cerdos rescatados, que ahora son libres de vivir una vida mejor en un santuario.
Como dijo el activista Wayne Hsiung durante el juicio, rescatar animales"no es lo peor de nosotros como seres humanos.Es lo mejor de nosotros".

Reconociendo que la comida vegana es "el futuro de la industria", el actor y cómico Kevin Hart ha lanzado un nuevo restaurante de comida rápida vegana llamadoHart Houseque pretende ofrecer una "experiencia culinaria innovadora que rompe las expectativas de lo que puede ser la comida basada en plantas".

Una nuevainvestigaciónha confirmado que la comida vegana para mascotas puede mantener a los perros e incluso a los gatos sanos y felices, reduciendo la enorme cantidad de daños que la comida tradicional para mascotas hace tanto a los animales como al medio ambiente.

La actriz Sadie Sink insta a "todo el mundo" a que considere la posibilidad de adoptar el veganismo al asociarse con Stella McCartney para promover los tejidos sostenibles y libres de crueldad en la moda. La estrella de Stranger Things es vegana desde los 14 años.
"La comida vegana es la comida del alma en su forma más auténtica. Comida del alma significa alimentar el alma. Y alimentar tu alma es tu intención. Si tu intención es pura, eres puro". Erykah Badu

Meet the most adorable calves, Clover, Rusty Braveheart, Buttercup, Phoenix Pipkin, and their brothers. They were born on a dairy farm and destined to be raised and slaughtered for veal because dairy and veal are inextricably linked. For these beautiful boys at least, it’s a very happy ending.

The GenV team members know how lucky we are to spend our days striving to make the world a better place. Here, we pool our advice for anyone who also wishes to make working for veganism their full-time job.

All over the world, lambs are slaughtered in their millions for Easter - the Christian festival of resurrection, hope, and life. To expose this appalling trade, our courageous Italian Country Managerwent to a slaughterhouseand was able to rescue one sweet baby, Eddie. See Eddie’s story.

Want to know the secrets of a long and happy life?! Meet Surendra Shah who became vegan at the age of 52 and is now a healthy, active 88-year-old.
We love to help and support people on their journey to veganism, but to create a vegan world, we need to better understand why people stop being vegan. Take a look!

Our food solidarity work continues and this month, with the support of local activist Justin Lumoo Paluku, we distributed 400 nutritious plant-based meals to people who've been displaced by the ongoing M23 rebellion (armed conflict) in Karisimbi, in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. We've also been providing daily meals for three vegans schools in Maasai Mara, Kenya, with the support of Maasai leader Jack Lekishon.Find outwhy food solidarity matters to us.

GenV will be speaking at Northeastern University London'sFossil Fuel Phase Out and Climate Futuresconference on Friday 21 April, about the climate and human health-related benefits of going vegan. You canregister to attend the conference here(in person or virtually).

We have news! Launching this weekend and rolling out across ten countries throughout May and beyond, Million Dollar Vegan is distributing $100,000 of vegan food to care workers, hospitals and the most vulnerable in our communities.

That means more than 100,000 plant-based meals will be delivered to hospitals in Italy and France, to homeless veterans in the US, to frontline care workers in Spain, and to underprivileged communities in Argentina, Brazil, Mexico, the UK and India. We will also be funding meals for 250 primary school children in Ethiopia for the next four months.

We’re doing this for two reasons. One, we want to do all we can to support the most vulnerable, and to provide them with great tasting, immunity-boosting healthy foods. But also, because the world must hear that this is a pandemic of our own making, and the very best way to make sure we do not have to go through this again is to go vegan.
Want to know more about our global food give-away?Read our blog here.

For years, experts have been warning us that a pandemic like COVID-19 – or worse, like the 1918 flu that killed an estimated 50-100 million people – would come, and that when it did it would be a virus of our own hatching.

Bird flu, swine flu, MERS, SARS, AIDS, Ebola and COVID-19 - and many more terrible diseases like tuberculosis, whooping cough, leprosy and typhoid - all came from our mistreatment of animals, both wild and farmed. And unless we change our behaviour, it is absolute certain that another pandemic will sweep the globe. Isn’t it time we understood that all life on Earth is connected?To preserve our own lives, we must also strive to preserve the lives of others.

Former hunter and army officer Mark Wakeling who was brought up within the meat trading world, has opened a sanctuary for farmed animals in the UK. Watch his moving story, and if you can afford a donation - or can share hiscrowdfunderwith others - you can help secure Amberwood Sanctuary for the future.

Anthony Mullally is a former professional international rugby league player. He is also vegan and runs men’s wellness retreats. We met with him to talk about men’s mental health, finding your place in the world, and what it is to be a man.

“I believe that toxic traits of masculinity have played a part in leading us down the path of over-consumption, domination of other species, and harm towards women and LGBTQIA+ groups. It has also led us to lose our connection with the natural world and spurred a silent crisis in men’s mental health.”
Read Joe Stratton’s blog on masculinity, strength, compassion, and veganism.

Temos muitas notícias importantes! Vamos começar celebrando o sucesso da nossa campanha “Ajude as Búfalas de Brotas”, mas também vamos pedir sua ajuda para acabar com o sofrimento terrível em uma fazenda de porcos na Inglaterra. Vamos lá?

A gente agradece a todo mundo que se inscreveu em um de nossos programas gratuitos sobre veganismo e ajudou a apoiar as mais de mil búfalas resgatadas em Brotas, interior de São Paulo. Para cada inscrição, a Geração Vegana doou US$ 1 para os santuários que cuidam desses animais, e estamos felizes em fazer a doação de US$ 10.000.
Esta campanha acabou, mas nossos programas gratuitos de 7 e 30 dias estão sempre disponíveis para te ajudar na sua jornada vegana.

Já conferiu a entrevista que fizemos com a guardiã do Santuário Vale da Rainha, Patrícia Varela? Ela contou para a gente a história das mais de mil búfalas abandonadas para morrer de fome e sede em Brotas, interior de São Paulo, que agora vivem em liberdade nos santuários Vale da Rainha e Rancho dos Gnomos. Não perca!

Recentemente, cineastas do Reino Unido visitaram uma grande fazenda de porcos, seis anos após a Animal Equality ter denunciado as condições terríveis do local. Apesar das promessas de melhorias feitas em 2017, nada mudou. Veja como são precárias as condições de "alto bem-estar" nas fazendas de porcos da Inglaterra.
Assista ao vídeoAVISO: não contém cena de violência explícita, mas o conteúdo é impactante. Ative as legendas em português.

Neste post escrito pela ativista vegana Alicia Griggs, que também é cristã, ela aponta que comer sem afetar os animais é uma característica fundamental das intenções originais de Deus em relação à humanidade, como podemos ver em Gênesis.

en el que conocemos una experiencia de veganismo popular en Argentina, compartimos nuestros mejores consejos para combinar veganismo y celiaquía, y celebramos todos los avances que nuestro movimiento ha conseguido para los animales, las personas y el planeta. Aquí llegó.

Te invitamos a conocer a María, cocinera popular de un asentamiento en situación de vulnerabilidad económica de la Ciudad de Buenos Aires, que logró veganizar el menú que comen muchas personas a diario, obteniendo la aprobación de su comunidad en Villa La Carbonilla. En sus palabras, el veganismo es rico y es posible para todes.

Hay consenso científico acerca de que los animales tienen sintiencia, que es la capacidad de acumular experiencias, definir si son positivas o negativas y en base a eso modificar su comportamiento. En varios países se está reavivando este debate para cambiar leyes que aún consideran a los animales como cosas y no como seres con subjetividad y derechos.

en el que analizamos algunos de los estereotipos y mitos en torno a la masculinidad, la identidad, la salud mental y el veganismo; una mamá vegana nos cuenta sus secretos de crianza y te traemos buenas noticias para alegrarte el día. ¡Sigue leyendo!

En este video Alba nos cuenta su experiencia de crianza vegana y lo mejor que nos comparte es que la manera más efectiva de que les niñes coman vegano es por el ejemplo de sus responsables de crianza. Ver a tu mamá o papá preparando y disfrutando la comida contigo, contándote los beneficios que tiene y que no hay crueldad en ella, es el mejor camino para que las infancias sigan nuestros pasos. Y por supuesto, encontrar buenos profesionales de la salud, con formación actualizada sobre estos temas, que acompañen las decisiones familiares.

"Creo que los rasgos tóxicos de la masculinidad han contribuido a llevarnos por el camino del consumo excesivo, la dominación de otras especies y el daño a las mujeres y a los grupos LGBTQIA+. También nos ha llevado a perder nuestra conexión con el mundo natural y ha estimulado una crisis silenciosa en la salud mental de los hombres".
Lee elblogde Joe Stratton sobre masculinidad, fuerza, compasión y veganismo.

Mark Wakeling, antiguo cazador y oficial del ejército criado en el mundo del comercio de la carne, ha abierto un santuario para animales de granja en el Reino Unido. Mira su conmovedora historia, y si puedes permitirte una donación -o puedes compartir su campaña de financiamiento colectivo- puedes ayudar a asegurar el futuro del Santuario de Amberwood.
Si has llegado hasta aquí, te agradecemos mucho la lectura y ¡te esperamos en nuestras redes sociales para mantenernos en contacto!
Si quieres probar el veganismo y no sabes por dónde empezar, puedes sumarte a nuestros Desafíos Veganos gratuitos ennuestra web.

Throughout January, we have continuedour food solidarity initiativesby supporting communities impacted by climate breakdown. In Kenya, where a drought has created a humanitarian crisis, we donated 45,000 meals to schoolchildren. In Argentina, where temperatures have reached an all-time high, we shared cooling fruits with children and adolescents. And in India, we went to Kerala, the state with the highest consumption of beef, to showcase some delicious and traditional vegan beef dishes. This is essential work given the impact of farmed cows on the climate.

Often, thoughtful people wishing to support communities in crisis donate a cow or goat  via NGOs like Oxfam and Christian Aid. This may be well-meant but it exacerbates the problems; it does not solve them. Cows need a lot of water, for example, which can put them in direct competition with people, and when droughts occur, the animals inevitably die. Our Kenya Country Manager Jack Lekishon reports that this is exactly what is happening right now. Plus, additional farmed animals place a greater burden on the climate, making those deadly droughts all the more likely. We support the Save Movement's campaign to end animal gifting and to implement plant-based projects instead. If you do, too, you can sign the petition here:

... in which we share an uplifting film from India, a powerful message from a former US farmer, and news of our work exposing pig farms in Mexico to the wider world. We are also asking for your help to protect Indigenous peoples and their land in Brazil. Read on.

Brazil’s lower house of Congress is dominated by agribusiness interests and it is about to vote on a bill which would legalize land-grabbing from Indigenous peoples. Not only is this a serious human rights abuse, but it will inevitably lead to further land degradation and increased animal farming, logging, and mining.

Help spread this information to bring international attention to this issue. Share theblog written by Brazilian activist Vitor Ávila, which explains what is happening in Brazil with the hashtag#MarcoTemporalNão.

A bold campaign calledEat Differentlyhas just launched. It features quotes from trailblazing luminaries of past and present who thought and ate differently, and hopes to inspire people to think differently about what they put on their plates.Eat Differentlywill be making waves in San Diego with the launch of 29 eye-catching billboards, and will expand to other cities in the U.S. throughout 2023.

All over the world, people are uniting against the oppression and environmental destruction wrought by animal agriculture. That’s why we were delighted to be at the Indore Animal Rights March in India, and to film some inspirational and eloquent activists there. Take a look!

A common accusation leveled at vegans by the farming industry is that they do not understand the farming system or rural traditions. But increasingly those from within the industry are speaking out, and even becoming vegan. We love this blog by former farmer, and current Social Media Coordinator for GenV, Simon Plazolles-Hayes.
